AGI -&nbsp; Britain and France will cooperate with Ukraine on a plan to end the fighting with Russia, which will then be presented to the US. British Premier Keir&nbsp;Starmer said so. "The United Kingdom, together with France and perhaps one or two others, will cooperate with Ukraine for a plan to end the fighting, and then discuss it with the United States," he said &nbsp;Starmer&nbsp; Bbc. For its part, Danish Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen said that the struggle for the freedom of Ukrainians is also that of Europe. "It is essential to ensure that Ukraine is strong and safe, so that we can achieve what we all want: a lasting and sustainable peace. Europe must be united and provide more military support. Better today than tomorrow. And we must ensure the necessary security guarantees so that the war does not return to Ukraine or any other country," he added.
<h2> The London summit
Supporting Ukraine, after the unprecedented clash between Volodymyr Zelensky and Donald Trump, but above all seeking unity among Europeans after Washington's 'strap'. More than a dozen European leaders gather today in London for crisis talks, in an attempt to increase security cooperation and aid in Kiev, in line with the two previous years' policy. The day after the White House clash, Ukrainian President was warmly welcomed to Downing Street. He twice embraced British Prime Minister Keir Starmer, promoter of today's meeting, in front of the cameras and obtained a loan to strengthen the impoverished defenses for over three years of war against the Russian invasion. "I thank the people and the government of the United Kingdom for their enormous support from the beginning of this war," said Zelensky. "We are happy to have such strategic partners and share the same vision as it should be a safe future for all."
Today the leader of Kiev will meet King Charles III before joining the European allies at the Security Summit.> The meeting involves leaders from all over continental Europe, including France, Germany, Denmark and Italy, as well as Turkey, NATO and the European Union. "Now is the time for us to join to ensure the best result for Ukraine, protect European security and ensure our collective future," said Starmer firmly convinced that today's summit is necessary for a "strong and lasting agreement that guarantees permanent peace" and to discuss "the next steps in planning solid security". With growing fears that the United States will continue to support NATO, the meeting in Britain will also address the need for Europe to increase defence cooperation.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Zelensky Saturday arrived in London welcomed by a crowd of supporters who applauded him. "You are very, very welcome here at Downing Street," said Starmer welcoming the Zelensky delegation before the closed door talks lasted 75 minutes. The two discussed the position of Ukraine and how to end the war "with a lasting and just peace that will not allow Russia to use ceasefire to rearm and attack again", according to a statement issued by Zelensky's office. To underline the economic commitment towards Kiev also a loan of 2,26 billion pounds >(2.74 billion euros) to support the ability to defend Ukraine, to be reimbursed with profits of the Russian sovereign assets immobilized. "The funds will be intended for weapons production in Ukraine," said Zelensky. "This is true justice: those who started the war must be the one who pays."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
In London there will also be the Italian premier, Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; who will have in the morning a bilateral meeting with Starmer, scheduled at 12 Italian hours at Downing Street, during which will address in particular the issue of war in Ukraine, the issue of irregular migration and cooperation in the field of Defense. In the afternoon, starting from the 15 Italians, the premier will participate to the summit. The meeting is a few days before the Extraordinary European Council, which will be dedicated to the same themes. "Every division of the West - it has declared&nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; which yesterday heard American President Donald Trump - makes us all weaker and favors who would like to see the decline of our civilization. Not of its power or its influence, but of the principles which founded it, first of all freedom. A division wouldn't suit anyone. We need an immediate summit between the United States, the European States and allies to speak frankly of how we intend to face today's great challenges, starting from Ukraine, which together we have defended in recent years, and of what we will be called to face in the future". &nbsp;
